        <h2 id="pros-cons">Pros and cons after 30 days</h2>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-card">
            <h4>✓ What Grammarly gets right</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Best-in-class real-time grammar accuracy</li>
              <li>Works everywhere you write — browser, desktop, mobile keyboard</li>
              <li>Clarity rewrites cut bloat 20–40% in seconds</li>
              <li>Tone detection saves emails from sounding rude</li>
              <li>Brand voice on Business tier is genuinely useful at scale</li>
              <li>GrammarlyGO is bundled at no extra cost</li>
              <li>Plagiarism checker covers 16B+ pages reliably</li>
              <li>Free tier catches 25% of issues — useful baseline</li>
              <li>Premium ($12/mo annual) pays for itself in week one</li>
              <li>Business tier adds analytics, snippet libraries, SSO</li>
            </ul>
