        <h2 id="verdict">Is Grammarly worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For individual writers: yes, Premium is a no-brainer.</strong> $12/mo (annual) for the best real-time editor on the market. Pays for itself in saved editing hours by Wednesday of week one.</p>

        <p><strong>For business teams: yes, Business at $15/seat is worth it once you're 5+ writers.</strong> Brand voice consistency alone justifies the upgrade. Below 5 seats, give everyone Premium and skip Business.</p>

        <p><strong>For SEO teams: yes — but understand what you're buying.</strong> Grammarly improves writing quality. It does not move rankings. Pair it with Surfer + research tools, or skip the DIY stack entirely and use done-for-you publishing.</p>

